abstract: The chip maker, which had a change in leadership this month, said it would beat analysts’ estimates.
snippet: The chip maker, which had a change in leadership this month, said it would beat analysts’ estimates.
lead_paragraph: Advanced Micro Devices, the second-largest maker of processors for personal computers after Intel, says sales this quarter will be higher than analysts’ estimates. Intel this month also indicated that demand for personal computers was improving.

headline.main: Advanced Micro Devices Predicts Strong Quarter
headline.print_headline: Advanced Micro Devices Predicts Strong Quarter
